  "prompt": "Who is the old man in the MDH Masala ads and why does he appear in all their ads?",
  "response": "The elderly man featured in the MDH Masala ads is **Mahashay Dharampal Gulati**, affectionately known as **\"Dharam Pal\"** or **\"MDH Uncle.\"** He was the chairman and face of MDH (Mahashay Di Hatti), a well-known Indian spice brand.\n\n### Why does he appear in all their ads?\n1. **Founder and Brand Ambassador**: Dharampal Gulati was not just the founder of MDH but also its most recognizable figure. He became the brand's ambassador, lending his face and credibility to the products. His presence in the ads was a way to personally vouch for the quality and authenticity of MDH spices.\n\n2. **Trust and Reliability**: His charismatic and grandfatherly image helped establish trust among consumers. People associated him with the brand's long-standing reputation for quality and tradition.\n\n3. **Memorable Marketing**: His unique style, energetic personality, and trademark glasses made the ads highly memorable. He became an iconic figure in Indian advertising, making MDH stand out in a competitive market.\n\nDharampal Gulati passed away in December 2020 at the age of 97, but his legacy continues to be associated with the MDH brand. Even after his demise, the company has continued to use his image in some ads, highlighting his enduring impact on the brand.",
